reviewText: This entire full stack developer course was just terrible. Sincerely, I feel like I have barely learned anything. This course is the most robotic and uninspired thing I've ever sat through. It just brushes over very huge concepts that no beginner is going to fully comprehend without doing extra research, yet the hands-on labs that are graded just expect you to remember it all and be a complete master at it. Along with that, having to sign up for multiple third-party sites to even begin some of the labs. Time to unsubscribe from all the spam mail I suppose! What makes this so bad is the fact that people have to PAY for this. You're telling me that courses like THESE are more industry recognized than something like Codecademy or FreeCodeCamp? Seriously? I've learned 100 times more from them and the best part about them is they're FREE. What an absolute joke this course was. Awful teaching. Awful labs. Awful videos. At least I know now not to bother giving Coursera any of my money next time.
You gave only courses name but not whole course content.
